Dreamed me and a girl I know had to go to high school class together. She said she had to go pick some delivery package at her home address, in the other part of town. I was always late for class anyways, so I got in her car and said I'd ride along with her. All done easily.

We spoke nothing, but she kept driving forwards. We entered another town, a smaller one. We knew we were never going back to the old town and to the school. Suddenly a bus appeared. She swerved the car to avoid it and we hit a pole. Both of us dead on the spot. It was Perfection.

We were driving afterwards, when I had the sudden realization the school and the town both did not matter at all to me. I told her not to make a turn back towards the school, but to keep driving forward. She knew what I meant. We left the town behind, there were grain fields now.
